            </p>

            <div class="about-block">
                <h2>Project Overview</h2>
                <p>
                    Smart Inventory Management System is a web-based application
                    designed to automate inventory operations and improve stock
                    control. The system provides real-time inventory tracking and
                    supports intelligent decision-making through data analysis.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="about-block">
                <h2>Key Features</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Real-time inventory and product management</li>
                    <li>Role-based access for Admin and Staff</li>
                    <li>Secure authentication and authorization</li>
                    <li>Sales and transaction recording</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="about-block">
                <h2>Apriori Algorithm Integration</h2>
                <p>
                    The system uses the <strong>Apriori Algorithm</strong> to analyze
                    historical sales data and identify frequently sold item sets.
                    This helps in forecasting product demand and supports better
                    restocking decisions.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="about-block">
                <h2>System Benefits</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Minimizes manual errors</li>
                    <li>Improves inventory accuracy</li>
                    <li>Saves time and operational cost</li>
                    <li>Enhances decision-making</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="about-block">
                <h2>Technologies Used</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Frontend: JSP, HTML, CSS</li>
                    <li>Backend: Java (Servlet & JSP)</li>
                    <li>Database: MySQL</li>
                    <li>Algorithm: Apriori Algorithm</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

        </div>
